      <folder name="Definitions" id="id-c5ed4e3d478647d2a511c9c3bcef1611">
        <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[definition] backup node" id="id-e637cdd2931c4cf18eee50212c149df0"/>
        <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[definition] dm node" id="id-81ad087a666e496bb24eb6dfbb12e5b3">
          <documentation>DM node is a node which uses Teradata Datamover utility. &#xD;
Technically - a node linked to target_system_code = 'DATAMOVER'</documentation>
        </element>
        <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[definition] HA node" id="id-1d1d81587d6d46e4b32907fd89a37439"/>
        <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[definition] running node" id="id-5b6b4cb28ca84eb685fd93911f0a7244">
          <documentation>It is a node which is currently in-progress state, which means from point of creating execution candidate till finish the execution by ending status (SUCU, SUCC, WARN, DQNS, FAIL) (excluded)</documentation>
        </element>
        <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[definition] backup blocking node" id="id-135c842550194f8d954078456a656ba1">
          <documentation>A virtual node created internally by OT. There is one such node for one tenant on which backup process is executed. The node transformation_id = '90000000000000002'. The node is linked to all transformation objects within the tenant. Consequently starting the node blocks all transformation objects within its tenant which effectively blocks triggering new processes for the tenant.</documentation>
        </element>
        <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[definition] Landing node" id="id-37af21487c744cb79586596e8511e4ff"/>
        <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[definition] non starting period" id="id-ad17dd231d094fd6a27a64e591c6b18c">
          <documentation>It is a time period which specifies for how long backup node waits for finishing other processes on the tenant until it is started. During the period all running nodes should be finished (a new not started) in order to assure correctness of the backup. It is defined in ot_dynamic_property with code: ????</documentation>
        </element>
        <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[definition] VIRTUAL_GATE node" id="id-be3925c819e94b83b0bb638b89c18c29">
          <documentation>It is a node which serves like GATE for nodes which must be aligned TOHLE SE MUSÍ DOPSAT. Execution of the VIRTUAL_GATE TOHLE SE MUSÍ DOPSAT</documentation>
        </element>
      </folder>
