    <folder name="x" id="id-c212365183324c7f944a0369b5141a9a">
      <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name=" yaml-validation-enabled" id="id-3fac04914e004e47bd66eb340905de72"/>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationService" name="[controller] resources" id="id-bf89fc34bbd446fc8b2ed064866a5bdd"/>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[file] $Trigger file" id="id-bf22ae557ab641b68df72e7cb5278742">
        <documentation>It is a empty file created in order to start execution of UAC workflow task. &#xD;
Its name is used for identification of the task and handover basic parameters.&#xD;
&#xD;
The name pattern for the trigger file is: {trfName} || ‘_’ || {trfID} || ‘_’ || FORMAT({busDate}, ‘YYYYMMDD’) || ‘_’ || {occ} || ‘.trigger’&#xD;
&#xD;
where&#xD;
{trfName} = popular name of workflow within UAC (dt_event.uac_workflow_name). &#xD;
There is an exception for landing nodes.For them it is determined from from landing table like {sandbox_code} || '_' || {full_file_name} - both from the associated landing record. If the landing record doesn't contain {sandbox_code} value 'SBXDEFAULT' is used.&#xD;
&#xD;
{trfID} = unique transformation ID known and set by developer (note: the transformation ID is unique in scope of tenant, but tenant ID is not part of the name, because the trigger file is generated into tenant's specific folder) (dt_event.transformation_id )&#xD;
{busDate} = Business date, for which the UAC workflow task should be executed&#xD;
{occ} = order number of execution of the trfID within tenant and business date (typically the number is 1, higher number means, that the execution is repeated)&#xD;
&#xD;
</documentation>
      </element>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="[folder] $Trigger file folder" id="id-505f53939c9d4a4cb44457213baa7184">
        <documentation>Trigger file folder is a filesystem folder on the orchestration server where the trigger files are generated. The default trigger file folder for the node's trigger file is specified in table dt_tenant. &#xD;
It is possible, that different trigger file folder is used. </documentation>
      </element>
