    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationEvent" name="end candidate triggering" id="id-9fa441d34881402194b767085aaa2542"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Block for exclusives" id="id-086c3dc0cbc548a98d3845e6824d51d1">
      <documentation>Description: The function blocks pools with running exclusive nodes before start processing candidates in order to not start any candidate without exclusive priority&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
&#xD;
{exPools} :=&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;sql>&#xD;
SELECT rn.target_pool_key, count(*)&#xD;
  FROM v_node_priority nf&#xD;
  JOIN v_running_nodes rn ON nf.dt_event_key = rn.dt_event_key&#xD;
  WHERE 1=1&#xD;
    AND nf.feature_value = 'EXCLUSIVE'&#xD;
  GROUP BY rn.target_pool_key;&#xD;
&lt;/sql>&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;for each {exPool}>&#xD;
&#xD;
˝˝0047b˝˝&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;/for each {exPool}>
</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Candidate's target system slots availability check" id="id-65588cdb68e4405c90da500166282855">
      <documentation>Description: The function eliminates candidate for which there is not enough slots available on its target system&#xD;
&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
˝˝0056a˝˝ like {systemSlot}&#xD;
&#xD;
if {systemSlot.available} &lt; {candidate.slotsNeeded} then ˝˝0056b˝˝</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Candidate's target pool slots availability check" id="id-bff3cd5b6717483483858741679bd68f">
      <documentation>Description: The function eliminates candidate in case when its target pool doesn't have enough slots to start the candidate.&#xD;
If a candidate has higher than standard priority and cannot be started for specifed time (starvation) due to lower priority nodes execution, function assures that lower priority nodes shouldn't be started in order to assure, that released slots will be available for the higher priority node&#xD;
&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
&lt;check whether candidate has fixed pool or floating floating pool>&#xD;
find a record ({candidatePool}) in «[register] poolSlots» where {candidatePool.target_pool_key} = {candidate.target_pool_key}&#xD;
if the {candidatePool.total} > 0 then {fixed} = TRUE&#xD;
&lt;/check whether candidate has fixed pool or floating floating pool>&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;check pool's slots availability for candidate with fixed pool>&#xD;
&lt;if {fixed} = TRUE>&#xD;
&lt;if {candidatePool.Available} is less than {candidate.slotsNeeded}>&#xD;
 then ˝˝0060a˝˝&#xD;
&lt;if if {candidate.priorityCode} less than 'STANDARD' and  {candidate.inserted_datetime} + {candidate.starvation_min} is less than current_timestamp>&#xD;
   ˝˝0060d˝˝&#xD;
&lt;/if {candidate.priorityCode} less than 'STANDARD' and  {candidate.inserted_datetime} + {candidate.starvation_min} is less than current_timestamp>&#xD;
&lt;/if {candidatePool.Available} is less than {candidate.slotsNeeded}>&#xD;
&lt;/if {fixed} = TRUE>&#xD;
&lt;/check pool's slots availability for candidate with fixed pool>&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;if {fixed} = FALSE (check pool's slots availability for candidate with floating pool)>&#xD;
-- Try to find a pool with higher or equal number of free slots than the candidate needs&#xD;
˝˝0060c˝˝ like {pools2Assign}&#xD;
&lt;for each pool2Assign where {candidate.slotsNeeded} is less than {pool2assign.available}>&#xD;
check priority: ˝˝0060g˝˝&#xD;
if record is found then {poolFound} = TRUE and leave the loop&#xD;
&lt;/for each pool2Assign where {candidate.slotsNeeded} is less than {pool2assign.available}>&#xD;
&lt;if {poolFound} = FALSE>&#xD;
˝˝0060b˝˝ &#xD;
&lt;if {candidate.priorityCode} less than 'STANDARD' and  {candidate.inserted_datetime} + {candidate.starvation_min} is less than current_timestamp>&#xD;
find all slots in the target system: ˝˝0060e˝˝ like {possPools}&#xD;
&lt;for each possPool>&#xD;
block the slot for lower priority:  ˝˝0060d˝˝&#xD;
&lt;/for each possPool>&#xD;
&lt;/if {candidate.priorityCode} less than 'STANDARD' and  {candidate.inserted_datetime} + {candidate.starvation_min} is less than current_timestamp>&#xD;
&lt;/if {poolFound} = FALSE>&#xD;
&lt;/if {fixed} = FALSE (check pool's slots availability for candidate with floating pool)>&#xD;
</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Candidate's node group slots availability check" id="id-2837255640f04412b33f94bd791b2972">
      <documentation>Description: The function determine defined resource groups for the candidate and then eliminates candidate in case when at least one resource group doesn't have enough slots for the candidate.&#xD;
&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
&lt;find a resource group the candidate belongs to>&#xD;
	{candidatesFilter}:= distinct {filterKey} from ˝˝0002˝˝&#xD;
&lt;/find a resource group the candidate belongs to>&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;for each {candidatesFilter} perform>&#xD;
	{filterResources} := ˝˝0003˝˝&#xD;
	&lt;for each {filterResource} perform>&#xD;
	 if {filterResources.resavailable} &lt;  {candidate.slotsNeeded}  then ˝˝0001˝˝ and leave the loop and the function&#xD;
	&lt;/for each {filterResource} perform>&#xD;
&lt;/for each {filterKey} perform></documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Candidate's target object availability check" id="id-d0cbd649899b498baa867d5a438304e6">
      <documentation>Description: The function eliminates candidate in case when its target database object is actually blocked by another transformation&#xD;
&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
˝˝0006˝˝&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;for each selected {neededTargetObject}>&#xD;
{lockedTargetObject} := ˝0005˝&#xD;
if {lockedTargetObject} is found and {lockedTargetObject.usageType} = 'WRITE'  then ˝0004˝ and leave the loop&#xD;
&lt;/for each selected {neededTargetObject}>&#xD;
</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="DM candidate's parallel tenant's dm run check" id="id-528e2658544d40b8ab8223c7738843bf">
      <documentation>Description: The function eliminates DM candidate in case when some DM node is running on the tenant OR backup node of the same tenant is running
&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
&lt;check another DM nodes running for tenant>&#xD;
˝˝0009˝˝&#xD;
if {{tenantDMSlots.dmUsed} > 0  THEN ˝˝0008˝˝ and leave the function&#xD;
&lt;/check another DM nodes running for tenant>&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;check running backup node on the tenant>&#xD;
˝˝0013˝˝&#xD;
if record in is found THEN ˝˝0014˝˝ and leave the function&#xD;
&lt;/check running backup node on the tenant>&#xD;
</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Backup blocking node for backup candidate check" id="id-adb855c2abad408cad358bf888def9b6">
      <documentation>Description: The function is proceed for BACKUP candidates only. It eliminates candidate when other backup node is in progress. Then blocks all required resources on the tenant in order to assure gradual finishing all transformation processes and not starting new for clear starting of backup process on the tenant. That's assured by using so called backup blocking node. The pretention is made only is not exist yet.&#xD;
&#xD;
&#xD;
&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
&#xD;
˝˝0015˝˝&#xD;
&#xD;
if {backupBlockerNode} found then leave the function&#xD;
&#xD;
˝˝0017˝˝&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;if {bckInProgress} found>&#xD;
&#xD;
˝˝0016˝˝ and leave the function&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;/if {bckInProgress} found>&#xD;
&#xD;
˝˝0018˝˝&#xD;
&#xD;
˝˝0019˝˝&#xD;
&#xD;
˝˝0020˝˝&#xD;
&#xD;
˝˝0021˝˝&#xD;
&#xD;
</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Tenant's availability for backup node start check" id="id-688570bd0f864baf83b306c8922d47f3">
      <documentation>Description: The function evaluates whether backup node can be triggered. It can be triggered in case when no other process is running on the tenant or when non-starting-period has passed&#xD;
&#xD;
&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
{backupBlockerNode} := ˝˝0023˝˝&#xD;
{runNode} := first record from ˝˝0022˝˝ &#xD;
{ntpEnd} := ˝˝0025˝˝&#xD;
&#xD;
&lt;if {ntpEnd} > current_timestamp and {runNode} is found>&#xD;
˝˝0024˝˝&#xD;
