    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="Runtime event - write" id="id-33c114ccc522409bb00fa9a42f12e4fe"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="pretendSuccExecution" id="id-4a2d40cc05db4c18a2829f9078106080">
      <documentation>Description: The function pretends that a virtual node has been successfully finished.&#xD;
&#xD;
Technically - to be added&#xD;
+ occurence determination to be added</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationProcess" name="Queue processing preparation" id="id-b0bc90fc2769448187c6d16bb5aedfd2">
      <documentation>Description: The subprocess retrieves neccessary data for queue processing from a database in order to save number of db interactions&#xD;
&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
1) ˝˝0045e˝˝&#xD;
&lt;if at least one {candidate} is found>&#xD;
2) ˝˝0045a˝˝&#xD;
3) ˝˝0045b˝˝&#xD;
4) ˝˝0045c˝˝&#xD;
5) ˝˝0045d˝˝&#xD;
6) ˝˝0045f˝˝&#xD;
7) ˝˝0045g˝˝&#xD;
8) ˝˝0045h˝˝&#xD;
9) ˝˝0045i˝˝&#xD;
&lt;if at least one {candidate} is found></documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationProcess" name="Queue processing finalization" id="id-0d6f8be5c916439d8ca36e80f07d8f3d">
      <documentation>Description: The process finish queue processing by update individual candidates within database&#xD;
&#xD;
&#xD;
Technically:&#xD;
˝˝0046x˝˝ - all records&#xD;
&lt;for each {candidate}> &#xD;
if {candidate.triggeringResult} = 'POSTPONE' then ˝˝0061˝˝&#xD;
&lt;if {candidate.triggeringResult} = '2TRIGGER'>&#xD;
&lt;occurrence determination>&#xD;
{occ2Trigger} := ˝˝0037˝˝&#xD;
{occ2Trigger} not found then {occ2Trigger} = 0&#xD;
{occ2Trigger} = {occ2Trigger} + 1&#xD;
&lt;/occurrence determination>&#xD;
&lt;if {candidate.nodeType} = 'VIRTUAL_GATE' (pretend execution)> &#xD;
˝˝0046e˝˝&#xD;
˝˝0035˝˝&#xD;
&lt;/if {candidate.nodeType} = 'VIRTUAL_GATE' (pretend execution)>&#xD;
&#xD;
if {candidate.nodeType} != 'VIRTUAL_GATE' ˝˝0046b˝˝&#xD;
&lt;/if {candidate.triggeringResult} = '2TRIGGER'>&#xD;
&lt;/for each {candidate}> </documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="getNodeKey" id="id-a6be115930be4fd8a049bff829c48d00">
      <documentation>Description: The function finds the key of node based on provided Transformation Id and tenant code or vice-versa.

Technically:
&lt;sql>
SELECT dt_event_key as eventKey, e.transformation_id as transformationId, t.identifier as tenantCode
FROM dt_event e
join dt_tenant t on t.dt_tenant_key = e.dt_tenant_key
where upper(t.identifier) = upper(coalesce(@tenantId, t.identifier))
and e.dt_event_key = coalesce(@nodeKey, e.dt_event_key)
and e.transformation_id = coalesce(@transformationId, e.transformation_id)
&lt;/sql></documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationFunction" name="validateLinkDefinition" id="id-fa27a5ae9362469d81e51329154cbebe">
      <documentation>Description: validate input nodes

Technically:
1) ˝˝0100c˝˝  with parameters: tenantId: = {linkRecord.fromTenant}, transformationId: = {linkRecord.fromNode} and use returned parameter like {fromNodeKey}
if {fromNodeKey} is not not found then {errorMessage} = {errorMessage} &amp; &quot;Invalid source (FROM) node :&quot; &amp; {linkRecord.fromTenant}  &amp; '/' &amp; {linkRecord.fromNode}

2) ˝˝0100c˝˝  with parameters: tenantId: = {linkRecord.toTenant}, transformationId: = {linkRecord.toNode} and use returned parameter like {toNodeKey}
if {toNodeKey} is not not found then {errorMessage} = {errorMessage} &amp; &quot;Invalid source (TO) node :&quot; &amp; {linkRecord.toTenant}  &amp; '/' &amp; {linkRecord.toNode}

3)
&lt;if {errorMessage} is empty>
&lt;sql>
select dt_event_link_key as linkKey,
obligatory_on_delivery as oOD,
obligatory_on_redelivery as oOR,
trigger_on_delivery as tOD,
trigger_on_redelivery as tOR
from dt_event_link
where dt_event_key_1 = {fromNodeKey}
and dt_event_key_2 = {toNodeKey}
&lt;/sql>
&lt;/if {errorMessage} is empty>

if {errorMessage} not empty ˝˝0100h˝˝
if {errorMessage} is empty ˝˝0100g˝˝</documentation>
    </element>
